This paper deals with extracting 3D models from 2D keypoint annotations in unconstrained images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and pose estimation. The method also accounts for partial occlusions and explicitly factors in viewpoint changes and object deformations, which are related to robotics (RO) and machine learning (LG) techniques. The paper introduces a novel regularization technique, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI) and optimization (GR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.GR.
